Greg Hardy has been suspended by the NFL for 10 games at the start of the 2015 season . 
  Hardy was convicted by a judge last July of beating, strangling and threatening to kill his ex-girlfriend Nicki Holder  . 
  The charges were later dropped and Hardy signed with the Dallas Cowboys . 
  He will not receive his salary for the first 10 games of the season . 
  The NFL announced today that Hardy will be suspended without pay for the 2015 NFL season . 
  This comes after a two-month investigation into an incident of domestic abuse that allegedly occurred last year . 
 